snippet: James Harden scored 10 of his 28 points in overtime and the Houston Rockets rallied from 12 points down with just over two minutes to play to win their 10th straight game, 111-109 over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Saturday night....
lead_paragraph: James Harden scored 10 of his 28 points in overtime and the Houston Rockets rallied from 12 points down with just over two minutes to play to win their 10th straight game, 111-109 over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Saturday night.

headline.main: Rockets Rally for 10th Straight Win, Stun Wolves in OT
headline.print_headline: Rockets Rally for 10th Straight Win, Stun Wolves in OT
